        <p data-uuid="d8236c5bc26f46f8805ce89b4a566273">The development of the printing press was a giant step forward in spreading new ideas. In the mid-1400s a German man, <dfn title="Gutenberg, Johannes">Johannes Gutenberg</dfn> (GOOT-uhn-berk), developed a printing press that used movable type. This allowed an entire page to be printed at once. For the first time in history, thousands of people could read the same books and share ideas about them.</p>
